Made this mini-guide for a few simple methods to get yous some gepee's fairly fast, ofc these aren't the best as I'm not gonna give the best methods away (for free at least) but here yous go :). Made by me ofc. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=77nRDoWI5QE I suck at making video's.. turn the audio up WAY LOUD and full-screen it rofl. Tested these all today, they all still work ^^ 51 views, 2 pieces of feedback:(?

item.title: Rs money making guide 410k-1m/hour
item.dc:creator: @Andrew_Ferguson The317Guy
item.description:
@Andrew_Ferguson wrote:

[quote=“Kidpaparoach, post:4, topic:409155”][quote author=ExtremeX-Scape™ link=topic=510438.msg3703992#msg3703992 date=1312924282]
Holy shit…
Remake that.

I can’t hear / see shit.
[/quote]
In all honesty, I cba. Its good enough quality to understand what to do, I’ll remake if it gets a fair few requests. Next guide(if this one gets positive feedback) will be of a much higher quality.

Basically, turn spider pouches into the scrolls. Pickup blue drag scales while alching at the same time so your gaining exp. Cannon drags in high range bonus gear so your dps is good and bring safe guards so you don’t die like you’ll notice when i get clawed i rocktail brewed. I didn’t bring a restore cause i was letting the cannon do the work.
Pretty simple stuff just explained.[/quote]
I put my computer speakers on max and only heard mumbling tbh. ._.

item.title: Rs money making guide 410k-1m/hour
item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

[quote=“Kidpaparoach, post:16, topic:409155”][quote author=reyx7 link=topic=510438.msg3705546#msg3705546 date=1313010872]

Why where u alching at the same time?

So I’m gaining exp while doing it, I tend not to do things that don’t give me any exp. It doesn’t really slow me down.

Out of curiousity, when did u start playing rs?
[/quote]
About 7 years ago but I was a noob for about 3 years(I started when I was 9, I’m 16 now) however. I’ve got a fair few accounts though, the account I’m using in the video is the one I’m using atm.

@Extreme, ofcofc but you can replace it by doing something else. Lets say bolt making, there’s so many things you can do while you run in Rs. Btw nice Mage.[/quote]
Oh ok. I just find that newer users to the game, generally those who played after the mass graphic updates, really changed the whole multitasking system, and how much faster they can level up. Games like castle wars weren’t fun (to them, I enjoy CWars greatly), so free items where added, ontop of the mini rewards it already gave. Same thing with how the dueling arena was made f2p. People wanted to level up faster without item risk against friends/others, so they made it optional to risk.
